# Extension JS Safety

- When changing rule generation, keep canonical storage and matching concerns separate:
  - canonical rule data in objects/storage
  - raw URL-safe matching in `regexFilter`
- Escape regex literals through a helper function instead of inline duplicated replace logic.
- If changing shared rule construction in one browser target, mirror equivalent behavior in the other target unless instructed otherwise.
- Do not assume encoded and decoded query key representations are interchangeable in raw URL regex matching.
- Prefer focused changes near `CustomRule`/`rule-management` instead of broad rewrites.
